Does the RStudio preview import interface work with the new fetter format?

00:41:14.000 --> 00:41:16.000
Ah, my goodness.

00:41:16.000 --> 00:41:19.000
Yes, I mean, no, but I would love to.

00:41:19.000 --> 00:41:23.000
So yeah, the fetter format is just a great file format.

00:41:23.000 --> 00:41:27.000
We didn't have a chance to talk about fetter today.

00:41:27.000 --> 00:41:36.000
For those of you that are listening, fetter is a new file format that is helping people interoperate between Python and R,

00:41:36.000 --> 00:41:42.000
and it's also designed with fast access in their design.

00:41:42.000 --> 00:41:44.000
So it's a very fast file format.

00:41:44.000 --> 00:41:47.000
Loading and saving data is very, very fast.

00:41:47.000 --> 00:41:49.000
I think it's just a great suggestion.

00:41:49.000 --> 00:41:52.000
Currently, no, there's no integration with the fetter format,

00:41:52.000 --> 00:41:56.000
but you can install fetter, the fetter package,

00:41:56.000 --> 00:42:01.000
and definitely search online for R fetter.

