00:43:41.000 --> 00:43:46.000
What I can say for this question is that the same approach that we use for distributed data

00:43:46.000 --> 00:43:53.000
would obviously work for cubes, where you extract the data that you're interested in from the system

00:43:53.000 --> 00:43:55.000
and then you import it into R.

00:43:55.000 --> 00:44:03.000
How about, another question, how about the meta information usually present in other packages' files,

